o3 Answer:
To obtain the inverse of a relation, interchange every ordered pair’s coordinates (swap x and y).

Original relation  
{(0, –2), (1, 3), (2, 7), (3, 12)}

Inverse (switch x and y)  
{(–2, 0), (3, 1), (7, 2), (12, 3)}

Domain of the inverse: the set of first coordinates  
{–2, 3, 7, 12}

Range of the inverse: the set of second coordinates  
{0, 1, 2, 3}

Since every first coordinate in the inverse is unique, the inverse is also a function.

